# Technical Spec Skill

Generate professional technical specification documents as self-contained HTML.

## Full Documentation

Read complete skill details from: `docs/skills/technical-spec-design.md`
Read theme CSS from: `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`

## Required Sections

1. **Overview** - Problem, solution summary, scope
2. **Background** - Context, existing systems, constraints
3. **Goals & Non-Goals** - What we will/won't solve
4. **Proposed Solution** - Detailed technical approach
5. **System Architecture** - Components, interactions
6. **Data Model** - Entities, relationships, schemas
7. **API Design** - Endpoints, contracts
8. **Security Considerations** - Auth, encryption, threats
9. **Performance Requirements** - SLAs, benchmarks
10. **Testing Strategy** - Unit, integration, e2e
11. **Rollout Plan** - Deployment phases
12. **Open Questions** - Unresolved decisions
13. **Alternatives Considered** - Why not chosen

## Key Components

- **Architecture diagrams** - Box-and-arrow system views
- **Sequence diagrams** - Request flows
- **Code blocks** - Syntax-highlighted examples
- **Decision tables** - Options with pros/cons
- **Timeline** - Implementation phases

## RFC Format (Optional)

```
RFC: [Number]
Title: [Feature Name]
Author: [Name]
Status: Draft | Review | Approved | Implemented
Created: [Date]
```

